WEBVTT

00:42.000 --> 00:44.419
Since you're in such a talkative mood,
come up and help me with this exercise.

00:47.255 --> 00:52.093
Students, in preparation
for your upcoming oral exam,

00:52.427 --> 00:55.096
let's work on your conversational Spanish.

00:55.597 --> 00:57.265
Who'd like to converse with Carolina?

00:59.350 --> 01:02.562
Carlos, come chat with your girlfriend.

01:07.067 --> 01:08.485
Señora O’Reilly,

01:09.569 --> 01:10.570
we...

01:11.529 --> 01:13.073
my and Carolina...

01:15.325 --> 01:16.409
we to break.

01:17.869 --> 01:18.703
We broke.

01:20.955 --> 01:24.501
We... no more love.

01:25.543 --> 01:27.712
Now... not together.

01:30.173 --> 01:32.175
Oh no! What happened?

01:33.426 --> 01:36.137
Maybe it was his difficult mother

01:36.221 --> 01:39.891
and her obsession with protecting
the family's sapphire business.

01:42.685 --> 01:43.603
What?

01:43.686 --> 01:46.773
Keep going.
I'm noodling on an idea for a telenovela.

01:51.861 --> 01:53.822
Hello, Carlos. You look nice today.

01:54.280 --> 01:55.698
How was your evening?

01:56.741 --> 01:57.909
Hi, Carolina.

01:58.910 --> 02:02.038
I had in a good day-- Night.

02:05.458 --> 02:07.418
I played guitar with my friends.

02:08.419 --> 02:09.838
Uh... Music.

02:10.380 --> 02:12.465
I am work. Worked?

02:13.007 --> 02:13.883
Working.

02:13.967 --> 02:18.721
I am working on a new song.

02:19.556 --> 02:20.807
Uh... That's great.

02:21.432 --> 02:23.476
I hope I can hear your song.

02:23.852 --> 02:25.061
What is it called?

02:25.645 --> 02:27.647
The song name is "Cozy Couch of You."

02:30.024 --> 02:33.236
What happened in your night?

02:37.490 --> 02:39.284
Chloe has worms.

02:39.868 --> 02:43.580
The pretty girl has many, many worms.

02:43.663 --> 02:45.081
-
-I'm sorry.

02:45.165 --> 02:45.999
It's okay.

02:46.082 --> 02:49.252
That flow state
is where the real learning happens.

02:49.752 --> 02:52.547
These skills will elevate you from basic

02:53.339 --> 02:54.549
to telenovela.

03:03.266 --> 03:07.687
Please take one and pass along.

14:26.031 --> 14:28.951
We're a few days away from your big exam.

14:29.034 --> 14:30.244
Let's switch up partners

14:30.327 --> 14:34.665
and see what discoveries await.

15:13.412 --> 15:17.625
It's so hot in Mexico this time of year.

15:18.417 --> 15:22.463
Would you like to join me
for an evening swim?

15:25.716 --> 15:27.509
I miss your family.

15:27.593 --> 15:30.095
My home and parents.

15:30.179 --> 15:32.097
-It's not great.
-Yes.

15:32.181 --> 15:33.724
How is Chloe?

15:33.807 --> 15:38.062
She still has many worms.

15:39.396 --> 15:40.606
That is so Chloe.
